="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle C\\bullet D:=\\sum _{r,s}\\langle \\langle C\\rangle _{r}\\langle D\\rangle _{s}\\rangle _{|s-r|}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b233f47fe98cd89a61095854a841327e64b5d984" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.338ex; width:28.217ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle C\\bullet D:=\\sum _{r,s}\\langle \\langle C\\rangle _{r}\\langle D\\rangle _{s}\\rangle _{|s-r|}}" /></span> &#160;&#160;(the "(fat) dot" product)<sup id="cite_ref-11" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-11">[b]</a></sup></dd>\n</dl>\n<p><a href="#CITEREFDorst2002">Dorst (2002)</a> makes an argument for the use of contractions in preference to Hestenes\'s inner product; they are algebraically more regular and have cleaner geometric interpretations. A number of identities incorporating the contractions are valid without restriction of their inputs. For example,</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>I</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>I</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle C\\;\\rfloor \\;D=(C\\wedge (DI^{-1}))I}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2fe508bead54e576aa34d45a6caf4715041b3c80" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.875ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle C\\;\\rfloor \\;D=(C\\wedge (DI^{-1}))I}" /></span></dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230A;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8a --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>I</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>I</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle C\\;\\lfloor \\;D=I((I^{-1}C)\\wedge D)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7672fe5a9ca577bb33a112631977c28b6868c7e8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.875ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle C\\;\\lfloor \\;D=I((I^{-1}C)\\wedge D)}" /></span></dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A\\;\\rfloor \\;(B\\;\\rfloor \\;C)=(A\\wedge B)\\;\\rfloor \\;C.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0175147a611debe987de4eb1b1050f8e7c614152" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:27.629ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle A\\;\\rfloor \\;(B\\;\\rfloor \\;C)=(A\\wedge B)\\;\\rfloor \\;C.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Benefits of using the left contraction as an extension of the inner product on vectors include that the identity <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle ab=a\\cdot b+a\\wedge b}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a415c23cbe6013e9b9556a630d0ca17f653ced57" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:16.987ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="ab=a\\cdot b+a\\wedge b" /></span> is extended to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle aB=a\\;\\rfloor \\;B+a\\wedge B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8922e35a07dfade823ac3caabeb1ee4ea6c1887a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:19.93ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle aB=a\\;\\rfloor \\;B+a\\wedge B}" /></span> for any vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> and multivector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>, and that the <a href="/wiki/Projection_(linear_algebra)" title="Projection (linear algebra)">projection</a> operation <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{b}(a)=(a\\cdot b^{-1})b}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/73ec8b7fe0dc1cbe99de015f86199b30fe2ccf07" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.876ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {P}}_{b}(a)=(a\\cdot b^{-1})b" /></span> is extended to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{-1})\\;\\rfloor \\;B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ab40209f8b1f73bd3e6d383bd3a0665f44e2dd63" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.954ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{-1})\\;\\rfloor \\;B}" /></span> for any blade <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> and any multivector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7daff47fa58cdfd29dc333def748ff5fa4c923e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.754ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="A" /></span> (with a minor modification to accommodate null <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>, given <a href="#Projection_and_rejection">below</a>).</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Terminology_specific_to_geometric_algebra">Terminology specific to geometric algebra</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Terminology specific to geometric algebra">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Some terms are used in geometric algebra with a meaning that differs from the use of those terms in other fields of mathematics. Some of these are listed here:</p>\n<dl>\n<dt>Vector</dt>\n<dd>In GA this refers to an element of the <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/92d98b82a3778f043108d4e20960a9193df57cbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="1" /></span>-vector subspace unless otherwise clear from the context, despite the entire algebra forming a <a href="/wiki/Vector_space" title="Vector space">vector space</a>.</dd>\n<dt>Grade</dt>\n<dd>When used in GA, this is a synonym for <i>degree</i> of a homogeneous element under the <a href="/wiki/Graded_algebra" class="mw-redirect" title="Graded algebra">grading as an algebra</a> with the exterior product (a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">Z</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/faf96082c4b2e79d67626f995ae571403f51b5da" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.431ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\\mathrm  {Z}}" /></span>-grading), and not under the geometric product.<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-12">[c]</a></sup></dd>\n<dt>Outer product</dt>\n<dd>When used in GA, this is a synonym for <i><a href="/wiki/Exterior_product" class="mw-redirect" title="Exterior product">exterior product</a></i>, the term used by many authors. It is not the <a href="/wiki/Outer_product" title="Outer product">outer product</a> of linear algebra.</dd>\n<dt>Inner product</dt>\n<dd>When used in GA, this is synonym for the <i>scalar product</i> of a <a href="/wiki/Pseudo-Euclidean_vector_space" class="mw-redirect" title="Pseudo-Euclidean vector space">pseudo-Euclidean vector space</a>, and refers to the symmetric bilinear form on the <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/92d98b82a3778f043108d4e20960a9193df57cbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="1" /></span>-vector subspace, not the <a href="/wiki/Inner_product" class="mw-redirect" title="Inner product">inner product</a> on a normed vector space. Some authors may extend the meaning of <i>inner product</i> to the entire algebra, but there is little consensus on this. Even in texts on geometric algebras, the term is not universally used.</dd>\n<dt>Versor</dt>\n<dd>In GA this refers to an element of the algebra that can be constructed as the geometric product of any number of non-null vectors; an element of the Clifford group. Elsewhere, the term <i><a href="/wiki/Versor" title="Versor">versor</a></i> may refer to a unit quaternion, which is analogous to a rotor in GA.</dd>\n<dt><a href="/wiki/Outermorphism" title="Outermorphism">Outermorphism</a></dt>\n<dd>In GA this refers to the extension of a linear map on the vector subspace that preserves the exterior product. It is unrelated to the contraction of <i>outer automorphism</i> that is sometimes used in group theory.</dd>\n</dl>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Geometric_interpretation">Geometric interpretation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Geometric interpretation">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Projection_and_rejection">Projection and rejection</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Projection and rejection">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg/300px-GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg.png" width="300" height="161" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg/450px-GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg/600px-GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="369" data-file-height="198" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:GA_plane_subspace_and_projection.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nIn 3-d space, a bivector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\land b}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ff8a40f76f4fd75aa92b1a78e44fb7f76ab6ed70" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:4.841ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle a\\land b}" /></span> defines a 2-d plane subspace (light blue, extends infinitely in indicated directions). Any vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>c</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/86a67b81c2de995bd608d5b2df50cd8cd7d92455" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.017ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="c" /></span> in 3-d space can be decomposed into its projection <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2225;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa5 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c_{\\|}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/dee7b4170f845f6466692e22538b653ea51aa192" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:2.079ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle c_{\\|}}" /></span> onto a plane and its rejection <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c_{\\perp }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5dd97009de24ad42bf4c13c31b9897887ff703be" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.535ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle c_{\\perp }}" /></span> from this plane.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>For any vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> and any invertible vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span>,</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x2225;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa5 --></mo>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a=amm^{-1}=(a\\cdot m+a\\wedge m)m^{-1}=a_{\\|m}+a_{\\perp m},}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3b37291ff4b2cd70a99f3c7b67801560c272a935" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:49.67ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle a=amm^{-1}=(a\\cdot m+a\\wedge m)m^{-1}=a_{\\|m}+a_{\\perp m},}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>where the <b>projection</b> of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> onto <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span> (or the parallel part) is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x2225;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa5 --></mo>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a_{\\|m}=(a\\cdot m)m^{-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/59aa963752e834406e2189be4e48db30a9effddc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:18.07ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle a_{\\|m}=(a\\cdot m)m^{-1}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and the <b>rejection</b> of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> from <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span> (or the orthogonal part) is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x2225;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa5 --></mo>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a_{\\perp m}=a-a_{\\|m}=(a\\wedge m)m^{-1}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b5e08f42aad72b329d899dc7869f5d6c51cd060c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:31.04ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle a_{\\perp m}=a-a_{\\|m}=(a\\wedge m)m^{-1}.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Using the concept of a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>k</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle k}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c3c9a2c7b599b37105512c5d570edc034056dd40" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.222ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="k" /></span>-blade <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> as representing a subspace of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>V</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle V}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/af0f6064540e84211d0ffe4dac72098adfa52845" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.798ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="V" /></span> and every multivector ultimately being expressed in terms of vectors, this generalizes to projection of a general multivector onto any invertible <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>k</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle k}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c3c9a2c7b599b37105512c5d570edc034056dd40" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.222ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="k" /></span>-blade <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> as<sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-13">[d]</a></sup></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{-1})\\;\\rfloor \\;B,}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e0bcbeec8b17cb5340d3b454f52529948034481b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:24.612ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{-1})\\;\\rfloor \\;B,}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>with the rejection being defined as</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msubsup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}^{\\perp }(A)=A-{\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/feb629931e684f4cc980a8a29f419fc69257a1dc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:21.911ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}^{\\perp }(A)=A-{\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A).}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>The projection and rejection generalize to null blades <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> by replacing the inverse <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B^{-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2bef55d3c9b9256fe8540b097950ea123f5684a3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:4.122ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="B^{-1}" /></span> with the pseudoinverse <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B^{+}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/731dc88dd44f84be3617c27615bcc6840c2aeeb0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.293ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="B^{{+}}" /></span> with respect to the contractive product.<sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-14">[e]</a></sup> The outcome of the projection coincides in both cases for non-null blades.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEDorst2007.C2.A73.6_p._85_15-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEDorst2007.C2.A73.6_p._85-15">[10]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPerwass2009.C2.A73.2.10.2_p._83_16-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEPerwass2009.C2.A73.2.10.2_p._83-16">[11]</a></sup> For null blades <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>, the definition of the projection given here with the first contraction rather than the second being onto the pseudoinverse should be used,<sup id="cite_ref-17" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-17">[f]</a></sup> as only then is the result necessarily in the subspace represented by <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEDorst2007.C2.A73.6_p._85_15-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEDorst2007.C2.A73.6_p._85-15">[10]</a></sup> The projection generalizes through linearity to general multivectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7daff47fa58cdfd29dc333def748ff5fa4c923e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.754ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="A" /></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-18" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-18">[g]</a></sup> The projection is not linear in <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> and does not generalize to objects <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> that are not blades.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Reflection">Reflection</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Reflection">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Householder_transformation" title="Householder transformation">Simple reflections</a> in a hyperplane are readily expressed in the algebra through conjugation with a single vector. These serve to generate the group of general <a href="/wiki/Rotoreflection" class="mw-redirect" title="Rotoreflection">rotoreflections</a> and <a href="/wiki/Rotation_(mathematics)" title="Rotation (mathematics)">rotations</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-19" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-19">[h]</a></sup></p>\n<div class="thumb tleft">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:GA_reflection_along_vector.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/GA_reflection_along_vector.svg/200px-GA_reflection_along_vector.svg.png" width="200" height="185" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/GA_reflection_along_vector.svg/300px-GA_reflection_along_vector.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/GA_reflection_along_vector.svg/400px-GA_reflection_along_vector.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="235" data-file-height="217" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:GA_reflection_along_vector.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nReflection of vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>c</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/86a67b81c2de995bd608d5b2df50cd8cd7d92455" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.017ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="c" /></span> along a vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span>. Only the component of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>c</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/86a67b81c2de995bd608d5b2df50cd8cd7d92455" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.017ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="c" /></span> parallel to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span> is negated.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The reflection <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c\'}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f295e32663780aa8800e3106dba9d6e04e57cdc6" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.709ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="c&#039;" /></span> of a vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>c</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/86a67b81c2de995bd608d5b2df50cd8cd7d92455" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.017ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="c" /></span> along a vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span>, or equivalently in the hyperplane orthogonal to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span>, is the same as negating the component of a vector parallel to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span>. The result of the reflection will be</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x2225;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa5 --></mo>\n              <mi>m</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n              <mi>m</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle c\'={-c_{\\|m}+c_{\\perp m}}={-(c\\cdot m)m^{-1}+(c\\wedge m)m^{-1}}={(-m\\cdot c-m\\wedge c)m^{-1}}=-mcm^{-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1dd103998f964bdda222f04541d6c58c598142f7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:84.477ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle c&#039;={-c_{\\|m}+c_{\\perp m}}={-(c\\cdot m)m^{-1}+(c\\wedge m)m^{-1}}={(-m\\cdot c-m\\wedge c)m^{-1}}=-mcm^{-1}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This is not the most general operation that may be regarded as a reflection when the dimension <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2265;<!-- \xe2\x89\xa5 --></mo>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n\\geq 4}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/25010fec4b0f68f1b46f49d14917d962acca0b16" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:5.687ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle n\\geq 4}" /></span>. A general reflection may be expressed as the composite of any odd number of single-axis reflections. Thus, a general reflection <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\'}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6cb64c0f02687512818f37839ce23ee049c37743" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.932ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="a&#039;" /></span> of a vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> may be written</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>M</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>M</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\mapsto a\'=-MaM^{-1},}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2e1d1b0a0ed457ac13429bf6aef7f5211681ce50" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:20.932ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle a\\mapsto a&#039;=-MaM^{-1},}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>where</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>M</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>p</mi>\n        <mi>q</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle M=pq\\cdots r}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/48a972b590e7882f355c60c4aae8401f2fd0474a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:12.388ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle M=pq\\cdots r}" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>M</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>p</mi>\n        <mi>q</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>q</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>p</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle M^{-1}=(pq\\cdots r)^{-1}=r^{-1}\\cdots q^{-1}p^{-1}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4429b809ee1f17a96a37cc9aa7585c8f8c851fd7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:36.616ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle M^{-1}=(pq\\cdots r)^{-1}=r^{-1}\\cdots q^{-1}p^{-1}.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>If we define the reflection along a non-null vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a07d98bb302f3856cbabc47b2b9016692e3f7bc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.051ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="m" /></span> of the product of vectors as the reflection of every vector in the product along the same vector, we get for any product of an odd number of vectors that, by way of example,</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (abc)\'=a\'b\'c\'=(-mam^{-1})(-mbm^{-1})(-mcm^{-1})=-ma(m^{-1}m)b(m^{-1}m)cm^{-1}=-mabcm^{-1}\\,}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/03894c94a50859195f31655297e4f2ee3a67aded" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:97.138ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="(abc)&#039;=a&#039;b&#039;c&#039;=(-mam^{-1})(-mbm^{-1})(-mcm^{-1})=-ma(m^{-1}m)b(m^{-1}m)cm^{-1}=-mabcm^{-1}\\," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and for the product of an even number of vectors that</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>d</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (abcd)\'=a\'b\'c\'d\'=(-mam^{-1})(-mbm^{-1})(-mcm^{-1})(-mdm^{-1})=mabcdm^{-1}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/42cd8579dd6d464633d40e9c5a4b658fdf297e72" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:80.086ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle (abcd)&#039;=a&#039;b&#039;c&#039;d&#039;=(-mam^{-1})(-mbm^{-1})(-mcm^{-1})(-mdm^{-1})=mabcdm^{-1}.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Using the concept of every multivector ultimately being expressed in terms of vectors, the reflection of a general multivector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7daff47fa58cdfd29dc333def748ff5fa4c923e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.754ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="A" /></span> using any reflection versor <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>M</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle M}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f82cade9898ced02fdd08712e5f0c0151758a0dd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.453ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="M" /></span> may be written</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mi>M</mi>\n        <mi>&#x03B1;<!-- \xce\xb1 --></mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>M</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A\\mapsto M\\alpha (A)M^{-1},}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7ef0be46bb30b08aa2e1f0e1ec2a7bef4bb463bb" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.427ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle A\\mapsto M\\alpha (A)M^{-1},}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03B1;<!-- \xce\xb1 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\alpha }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b79333175c8b3f0840bfb4ec41b8072c83ea88d3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.498ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="\\alpha " /></span> is the <a href="/wiki/Automorphism" title="Automorphism">automorphism</a> of <a href="/wiki/Reflection_through_the_origin" class="mw-redirect" title="Reflection through the origin">reflection through the origin</a> of the vector space (<span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle v\\mapsto -v}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3015bb22251c5b50b8dcf9627ef7a50041b85d2d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:7.719ex; height:1.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle v\\mapsto -v}" /></span>) extended through linearity to the whole algebra.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Rotations">Rotations</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Rotations">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:GA_planar_rotations.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/GA_planar_rotations.svg/200px-GA_planar_rotations.svg.png" width="200" height="286" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/GA_planar_rotations.svg/300px-GA_planar_rotations.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/GA_planar_rotations.svg/400px-GA_planar_rotations.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="336" data-file-height="481" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:GA_planar_rotations.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nA rotor that rotates vectors in a plane rotates vectors through angle <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\theta }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6e5ab2664b422d53eb0c7df3b87e1360d75ad9af" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.101ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\theta " /></span>, that is <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle x\\mapsto R_{\\theta }xR_{\\theta }^{\\dagger }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cc0c58610cddb312c5f36616ae5ee69157821d56" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:11.875ex; height:3.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle x\\mapsto R_{\\theta }xR_{\\theta }^{\\dagger }}" /></span> is a rotation of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle x}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/87f9e315fd7e2ba406057a97300593c4802b53e4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.34ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="x" /></span> through angle <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\theta }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6e5ab2664b422d53eb0c7df3b87e1360d75ad9af" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.101ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\theta " /></span>. The angle between <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>u</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle u}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c3e6bb763d22c20916ed4f0bb6bd49d7470cffd8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.34ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="u" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle v}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e07b00e7fc0847fbd16391c778d65bc25c452597" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.138ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="v" /></span> is <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\theta /2}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/74af4b205463ab5f0642165e85d0b372ff42d442" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:3.447ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\theta /2" /></span>. Similar interpretations are valid for a general multivector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>X</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle X}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/68baa052181f707c662844a465bfeeb135e82bab" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.99ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="X" /></span> instead of the vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle x}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/87f9e315fd7e2ba406057a97300593c4802b53e4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.34ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="x" /></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-autogenerated1_7-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-autogenerated1-7">[6]</a></sup></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>If we have a product of vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle R=a_{1}a_{2}\\cdots a_{r}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/af55407842f281793b6ed17ad25a3bb2b4f485aa" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:15.216ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle R=a_{1}a_{2}\\cdots a_{r}}" /></span> then we denote the reverse as</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle R^{\\dagger }=(a_{1}a_{2}\\cdots a_{r})^{\\dagger }=a_{r}\\cdots a_{2}a_{1}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/42bc99e334841325650f660a7a767ad5b6091867" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:33.085ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle R^{\\dagger }=(a_{1}a_{2}\\cdots a_{r})^{\\dagger }=a_{r}\\cdots a_{2}a_{1}.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>As an example, assume that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle R=ab}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2a98cb91a49c6e4edd6070cfb61e8fc24ee0274d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:7.132ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="R=ab" /></span> we get</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle RR^{\\dagger }=abba=ab^{2}a=a^{2}b^{2}=ba^{2}b=baab=R^{\\dagger }R.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/20679d7ba60efdd37e7e21b4ab10be0007435bd3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:50.581ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle RR^{\\dagger }=abba=ab^{2}a=a^{2}b^{2}=ba^{2}b=baab=R^{\\dagger }R.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Scaling <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle R}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4b0bfb3769bf24d80e15374dc37b0441e2616e33" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="R" /></span> so that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle RR^{\\dagger }=1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/97f7dc82861d56ac39a575200e8b1533ca846842" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:8.8ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle RR^{\\dagger }=1}" /></span> then</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (RvR^{\\dagger })^{2}=Rv^{2}R^{\\dagger }=v^{2}RR^{\\dagger }=v^{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/17311ceb9168a701a68a727d91c66799a201b926" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:33.511ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle (RvR^{\\dagger })^{2}=Rv^{2}R^{\\dagger }=v^{2}RR^{\\dagger }=v^{2}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>so <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle RvR^{\\dagger }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/81a64ff4d7d6c597656395c2736c71203cc3e6a9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:5.657ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle RvR^{\\dagger }}" /></span> leaves the length of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle v}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e07b00e7fc0847fbd16391c778d65bc25c452597" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.138ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="v" /></span> unchanged. We can also show that</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (Rv_{1}R^{\\dagger })\\cdot (Rv_{2}R^{\\dagger })=v_{1}\\cdot v_{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c915d19dfe0c20b4f288da73b263b4b1b21e34b0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:27.984ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle (Rv_{1}R^{\\dagger })\\cdot (Rv_{2}R^{\\dagger })=v_{1}\\cdot v_{2}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>so the transformation <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle RvR^{\\dagger }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/81a64ff4d7d6c597656395c2736c71203cc3e6a9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:5.657ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle RvR^{\\dagger }}" /></span> preserves both length and angle. It therefore can be identified as a rotation or rotoreflection; <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle R}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4b0bfb3769bf24d80e15374dc37b0441e2616e33" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="R" /></span> is called a <a href="/wiki/Rotor_(mathematics)" title="Rotor (mathematics)">rotor</a> if it is a <a href="/wiki/Proper_rotation" class="mw-redirect" title="Proper rotation">proper rotation</a> (as it is if it can be expressed as a product of an even number of vectors) and is an instance of what is known in GA as a <i><a href="/wiki/Versor" title="Versor">versor</a></i> (presumably for historical reasons).</p>\n<p>There is a general method for rotating a vector involving the formation of a multivector of the form <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mi>B</mi>\n            <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mo>/</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle R=e^{-B\\theta /2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0975534b8579d7693ac51fdd27ce018e9ca280f9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:11.187ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle R=e^{-B\\theta /2}}" /></span> that produces a rotation <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\theta }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6e5ab2664b422d53eb0c7df3b87e1360d75ad9af" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.101ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\theta " /></span> in the plane and with the orientation defined by a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 2}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/901fc910c19990d0dbaaefe4726ceb1a4e217a0f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="2" /></span>-blade <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>.</p>\n<p>Rotors are a generalization of quaternions to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.405ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="n" /></span>-dimensional spaces.</p>\n<p>For more about reflections, rotations and "sandwiching" products like <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle RvR^{\\dagger }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/81a64ff4d7d6c597656395c2736c71203cc3e6a9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:5.657ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle RvR^{\\dagger }}" /></span> see <a href="/wiki/Plane_of_rotation" title="Plane of rotation">Plane of rotation</a>.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Hypervolume_of_a_parallelotope_spanned_by_vectors">Hypervolume of a parallelotope spanned by vectors</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Hypervolume of a parallelotope spanned by vectors">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>For vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle b}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f11423fbb2e967f986e36804a8ae4271734917c3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.008ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="b" /></span> spanning a parallelogram we have</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\wedge b=((a\\wedge b)b^{-1})b=a_{\\perp b}b}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/71c47c425d0c847910b59d4ac53257600ba7af4c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:28.404ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="a\\wedge b=((a\\wedge b)b^{-1})b=a_{\\perp b}b" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>with the result that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\wedge b}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1dc496a5b5da3e9b94eb72f04a54167dfe022e45" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:4.841ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="a\\wedge b" /></span> is linear in the product of the "altitude" and the "base" of the parallelogram, that is, its area.</p>\n<p>Similar interpretations are true for any number of vectors spanning an <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.405ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="n" /></span>-dimensional <a href="/wiki/Parallelepiped#Parallelotope" title="Parallelepiped">parallelotope</a>; the exterior product of vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2026;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a_{1},a_{2},\\ldots ,a_{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4e7dfb41e027e24804c6acd07429ef1158f29b60" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:13.324ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle a_{1},a_{2},\\ldots ,a_{n}}" /></span>, that is <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <munderover>\n            <mo>&#x22C0;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x80 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo>=</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </munderover>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>i</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle \\bigwedge _{i=1}^{n}a_{i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9494857a44852536db60c3c7d3552cb8680f4216" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:7.303ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\textstyle \\bigwedge _{i=1}^{n}a_{i}}" /></span>, has a magnitude equal to the volume of the <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.405ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="n" /></span>-parallelotope. An <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.405ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="n" /></span>-vector does not necessarily have a shape of a parallelotope \xe2\x80\x93 this is a convenient visualization. It could be any shape, although the volume equals that of the parallelotope.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Linear_functions">Linear functions</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Linear functions">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>An important class of functions of multivectors are the <a href="/wiki/Linear_function" title="Linear function">linear functions</a> that map multivectors to multivectors. The geometric algebra of an <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.405ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="n" /></span>-dimensional vector space is spanned by a basis of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 2^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8226f30650ee4fe4e640c6d2798127e80e9c160d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.399ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="2^{n}" /></span> elements. If a multivector is represented by a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 2^{n}\\times 1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/19db3bf36e5902a41f55a51e205d1909552aa1bf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:6.423ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle 2^{n}\\times 1}" /></span> real <a href="/wiki/Column_matrix" class="mw-redirect" title="Column matrix">column matrix</a> in terms of a basis, then all linear transformations of the multivector can be expressed as the <a href="/wiki/Matrix_multiplication" title="Matrix multiplication">matrix multiplication</a> by a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 2^{n}\\times 2^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/224a4a2c00116d57f7d93bd1116d1518837f1c28" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:7.648ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="2^{n}\\times 2^{n}" /></span> real matrix. However, such a general linear transformation allows arbitrary exchanges among grades, such as a "rotation" of a scalar into a vector, which has no evident geometric interpretation.</p>\n<p>A general linear transformation from vectors to vectors is of interest. With the natural restriction to preserving the induced exterior algebra, the <i><a href="/wiki/Outermorphism" title="Outermorphism">outermorphism</a></i> of the linear transformation is its unique extension. If <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>f</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle f}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/132e57acb643253e7810ee9702d9581f159a1c61" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.289ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="f" /></span> is a linear function that maps vectors to vectors, then its outermorphism is the function that obeys the rule</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <munder>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">f</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>&#x005F;<!-- _ --></mo>\n          </munder>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\underline {\\mathsf {f}}}(a_{1}\\wedge a_{2}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge a_{r})=f(a_{1})\\wedge f(a_{2})\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge f(a_{r})}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a90fbe9b68fda0b8914b10b5b788335b44649fd8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.604ex; margin-bottom: -0.734ex; width:50.729ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {\\underline {\\mathsf {f}}}(a_{1}\\wedge a_{2}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge a_{r})=f(a_{1})\\wedge f(a_{2})\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge f(a_{r})}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>for a blade, extended to the whole algebra through linearity.</p>\n<p>In the cases of reflections and rotations, their outermorphisms have a particularly simple algebraic form. Specifically, a mapping of vectors of the form</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x2192;<!-- \xe2\x86\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>:</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle V\\to V:a\\mapsto RaR^{-1},}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6f05ece7a6241045272124cb43bb4a4f6594deca" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:21.826ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle V\\to V:a\\mapsto RaR^{-1},}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>extends to the outermorphism</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x2192;<!-- \xe2\x86\x92 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>:</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mi>R</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(V)\\to {\\mathcal {G}}(V):A\\mapsto RAR^{-1}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/48c91f16a03c2917ef024906d78f5adcc5036579" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:29.319ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(V)\\to {\\mathcal {G}}(V):A\\mapsto RAR^{-1}.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Examples_and_applications">Examples and applications</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Examples and applications">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Intersection_of_a_line_and_a_plane">Intersection of a line and a plane</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Intersection of a line and a plane">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:LinePlaneIntersect.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/LinePlaneIntersect.png/220px-LinePlaneIntersect.png" width="220" height="122" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/LinePlaneIntersect.png/330px-LinePlaneIntersect.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/LinePlaneIntersect.png/440px-LinePlaneIntersect.png 2x" data-file-width="477" data-file-height="265" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:LinePlaneIntersect.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nA line L defined by points T and P (which we seek) and a plane defined by a bivector B containing points P and Q.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>We may define the line parametrically by <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>p</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B1;<!-- \xce\xb1 --></mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle p=t+\\alpha \\ v}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/be9c9a59553930f16f8cde1faf6b1224fab3192c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.079ex; width:11.285ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="p=t+\\alpha \\ v" /></span> where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>p</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle p}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/81eac1e205430d1f40810df36a0edffdc367af36" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.079ex; width:1.259ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="p" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle t}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/65658b7b223af9e1acc877d848888ecdb4466560" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:0.85ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="t" /></span> are position vectors for points T and P and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle v}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e07b00e7fc0847fbd16391c778d65bc25c452597" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.138ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="v" /></span> is the direction vector for the line.</p>\n<p>Then</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>p</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>q</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B\\wedge (p-q)=0}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/32e03d384bf9c78a618f8c9c4eeff927c2471618" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:15.59ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="B\\wedge (p-q)=0" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B1;<!-- \xce\xb1 --></mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>q</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B\\wedge (t+\\alpha v-q)=0}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/02becbddb8213dda09370f5492826b3b9da7e9ba" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:20.747ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="B\\wedge (t+\\alpha v-q)=0" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>so</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03B1;<!-- \xce\xb1 --></mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>B</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mi>q</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>B</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n              <mi>v</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\alpha ={\\frac {B\\wedge (q-t)}{B\\wedge v}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d0b10d7c4b465de030a60f6a5b2f01e21f3b450e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:16.422ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="\\alpha ={\\frac {B\\wedge (q-t)}{B\\wedge v}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>p</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>B</mi>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>q</mi>\n                <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                <mi>t</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>B</mi>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mi>v</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle p=t+\\left({\\frac {B\\wedge (q-t)}{B\\wedge v}}\\right)v.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ddc62d66389da1fd7c73dff73526fca92105f813" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; margin-left: -0.079ex; width:25.508ex; height:6.343ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle p=t+\\left({\\frac {B\\wedge (q-t)}{B\\wedge v}}\\right)v.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Rotating_systems">Rotating systems</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Rotating systems">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The mathematical description of rotational forces such as <a href="/wiki/Torque" title="Torque">torque</a> and <a href="/wiki/Angular_momentum" title="Angular momentum">angular momentum</a> often makes use of the <a href="/wiki/Cross_product" title="Cross product">cross product</a> of <a href="/wiki/Vector_calculus" title="Vector calculus">vector calculus</a> in three dimensions with a convention of orientation (handedness).</p>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg/220px-Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg.png" width="220" height="203" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg/330px-Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg/440px-Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="231" data-file-height="213" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Exterior_calc_cross_product.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nThe cross product in relation to the exterior product. In red are the unit normal vector, and the "parallel" unit bivector.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The cross product can be viewed in terms of the exterior product allowing a more natural geometric interpretation of the cross product as a bivector using the <a href="/wiki/Hodge_dual" class="mw-redirect" title="Hodge dual">dual</a> relationship</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>I</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\times b=-I(a\\wedge b).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/25c3fe5d0b0d31e9131a2dc4d8e603ad0df4a992" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.538ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle a\\times b=-I(a\\wedge b).}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>For example, torque is generally defined as the magnitude of the perpendicular force component times distance, or work per unit angle.</p>\n<p>Suppose a circular path in an arbitrary plane containing orthonormal vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\hat {u}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/28b0daee3e5310b67eb2222b45bea6236d002c69" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.34ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\\hat {u}}" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>v</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\hat {v}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2790b6cafab4cc0f98a9ae8beb550947e60062f1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.237ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\\hat {v}}" /></span> is parameterized by angle.</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>cos</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>v</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>sin</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>cos</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>v</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>sin</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathbf {r} =r({\\hat {u}}\\cos \\theta +{\\hat {v}}\\sin \\theta )=r{\\hat {u}}(\\cos \\theta +{\\hat {u}}{\\hat {v}}\\sin \\theta )}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/792eb06a7b0823387e124c11da65bb10d2077631" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:44.478ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\mathbf {r} =r({\\hat {u}}\\cos \\theta +{\\hat {v}}\\sin \\theta )=r{\\hat {u}}(\\cos \\theta +{\\hat {u}}{\\hat {v}}\\sin \\theta )}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>By designating the unit bivector of this plane as the imaginary number</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi>i</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>v</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>v</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {i}={\\hat {u}}{\\hat {v}}={\\hat {u}}\\wedge {\\hat {v}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c995742858ac4f932065eca5509ed357e8f32a04" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:14.779ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {i}={\\hat {u}}{\\hat {v}}={\\hat {u}}\\wedge {\\hat {v}}}" /></span></dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>i</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle i^{2}=-1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/88e98a401d352e5037d5043028e2d7f449e83fa6" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:7.975ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle i^{2}=-1}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>this path vector can be conveniently written in complex exponential form</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathbf {r} =r{\\hat {u}}e^{i\\theta }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1969a2cac9914ea02707f78d37eb165d39e4daee" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:9.3ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\mathbf {r} =r{\\hat {u}}e^{i\\theta }}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and the derivative with respect to angle is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\frac {d\\mathbf {r} }{d\\theta }}=r{\\hat {u}}ie^{i\\theta }=\\mathbf {r} i.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d7fb75ccc9e777c560ab2499058e8fd2e97cc3cd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:17.867ex; height:5.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {\\frac {d\\mathbf {r} }{d\\theta }}=r{\\hat {u}}ie^{i\\theta }=\\mathbf {r} i.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>So the torque, the rate of change of work <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>W</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle W}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/54a9c4c547f4d6111f81946cad242b18298d70b7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.446ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="W" /></span>, due to a force <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/545fd099af8541605f7ee55f08225526be88ce57" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.751ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="F" /></span>, is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03C4;<!-- \xcf\x84 --></mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mi>W</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mi>&#x03B8;<!-- \xce\xb8 --></mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\tau ={\\frac {dW}{d\\theta }}=F\\cdot {\\frac {dr}{d\\theta }}=F\\cdot (\\mathbf {r} i).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/26056f13cc9502a0a446c78a26299d2a9bdf8210" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:29.505ex; height:5.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\tau ={\\frac {dW}{d\\theta }}=F\\cdot {\\frac {dr}{d\\theta }}=F\\cdot (\\mathbf {r} i).}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Unlike the cross product description of torque, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03C4;<!-- \xcf\x84 --></mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\tau =\\mathbf {r} \\times F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/724449f9f8b520bda2f5ee8772d46b98caa5fe92" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:10.036ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\tau =\\mathbf {r} \\times F" /></span>, the geometric algebra description does not introduce a vector in the normal direction; a vector that does not exist in two and that is not unique in greater than three dimensions. The unit bivector describes the plane and the orientation of the rotation, and the sense of the rotation is relative to the angle between the vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>u</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\hat {u}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/28b0daee3e5310b67eb2222b45bea6236d002c69" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.34ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\\hat {u}}" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>v</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\hat {v}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2790b6cafab4cc0f98a9ae8beb550947e60062f1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.237ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\\hat {v}}" /></span>.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Electrodynamics_and_special_relativity">Electrodynamics and special relativity</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Electrodynamics and special relativity">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In physics, the main applications are the geometric algebra of <a href="/wiki/Minkowski_spacetime" class="mw-redirect" title="Minkowski spacetime">Minkowski 3+1 spacetime</a>, <span class="nowrap">Cl<sub>1,3</sub></span>, called <a href="/wiki/Spacetime_algebra" title="Spacetime algebra">spacetime algebra</a> (STA),<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHestenes1966_5-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEHestenes1966-5">[5]</a></sup> or less commonly, <span class="nowrap">Cl<sub>3,0</sub>(<b>R</b>)</span>, called the <a href="/wiki/Algebra_of_physical_space" title="Algebra of physical space">algebra of physical space</a> (APS), where <span class="nowrap">Cl<sub>3,0</sub>(<b>R</b>)</span> is isomorphic to the <i>even</i> subalgebra of the 3+1 Clifford algebra, <span class="nowrap">Cl<span style="display:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height:1em;font-size:80%;text-align:left">[0]<br />\n3,1</span>(<b>R</b>)</span>.</p>\n<p>While in STA points of spacetime are represented simply by vectors, in APS, points of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (3+1)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/14fa08a45717e60128330e5efc428e109d41f42d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:7.027ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle (3+1)}" /></span>-dimensional spacetime are instead represented by <a href="/wiki/Paravector" title="Paravector">paravectors</a>: a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 3}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/991e33c6e207b12546f15bdfee8b5726eafbbb2f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="3" /></span>-dimensional vector (space) plus a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/92d98b82a3778f043108d4e20960a9193df57cbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="1" /></span>-dimensional scalar (time).</p>\n<p>In spacetime algebra the electromagnetic field tensor has a bivector representation <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi>F</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi>E</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi>B</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {F}=({E}+ic{B})\\gamma _{0}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3cdf6043bdf70a06cfb1b7a48ee3de774c1fed84" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.208ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {F}=({E}+ic{B})\\gamma _{0}}" /></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-20" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-20">[12]</a></sup> Here, the <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle i=\\gamma _{0}\\gamma _{1}\\gamma _{2}\\gamma _{3}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ecc2bbc0ad4b6347d549f0c552a7aff089c3c3e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:13.027ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle i=\\gamma _{0}\\gamma _{1}\\gamma _{2}\\gamma _{3}}" /></span> is the unit pseudoscalar (or four-dimensional volume element), <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\gamma _{0}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/407f2fbc64e21bb432f397fdb816de0f5083d900" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:2.276ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\gamma _{0}" /></span> is the unit vector in time direction, and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>E</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle E}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4232c9de2ee3eec0a9c0a19b15ab92daa6223f9b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.786ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="E" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> are the classic electric and magnetic field vectors (with a zero time component). Using the <a href="/wiki/Four-current" title="Four-current">four-current</a> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi>J</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {J}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b0cc3b0e4148791d4467dcf1e517f525590178d5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.482ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{J}" /></span>, <a href="/wiki/Maxwell%27s_equations" title="Maxwell\'s equations">Maxwell\'s equations</a> then become</p>\n<dl>\n<dd>\n<table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;">\n<tr>\n<th scope="column" style="width:160px;">Formulation</th>\n<th>Homogeneous equations</th>\n<th>Non-homogeneous equations</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="2">Fields</th>\n<td colspan="2"><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03BC;<!-- \xce\xbc --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>J</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle DF=\\mu _{0}J}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/05ab8dce2f5eb7bb7f15bb2745fd1784ebc684ce" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:10.75ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="DF=\\mu _{0}J" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D\\wedge F=0}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d67d7f35fa01b93000c7a3770b6771f9695a00f0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:10.561ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="D\\wedge F=0" /></span></td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03BC;<!-- \xce\xbc --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>J</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D\\cdot F=\\mu _{0}J}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8e999d1e259182897050235bfcc4e9965dcebe3c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:12.44ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="D\\cdot F=\\mu _{0}J" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Potentials (any gauge)</th>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F=D\\wedge A}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/56e7064ac32e76e3a3af4161fcfe741afffd2a22" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:11.141ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="F=D\\wedge A" /></span></td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03BC;<!-- \xce\xbc --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>J</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D\\cdot D\\wedge A=\\mu _{0}J}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/29157dda855d81e0d133d270edbc6818fc1c5621" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:16.97ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="D\\cdot D\\wedge A=\\mu _{0}J" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Potentials (Lorenz&#160;gauge)</th>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F=DA}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cbec005772bb69be7f71bdc19f1ab31575756069" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:8.548ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="F=DA" /></span>\n<p><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D\\cdot A=0}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/01dac8fb28339519c62766fc372cf3a4a9fa5e71" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:9.66ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="D\\cdot A=0" /></span></p>\n</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>D</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03BC;<!-- \xce\xbc --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>J</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D^{2}A=\\mu _{0}J}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/96efe647da67c2f23a8c54f81cee1d356578fb2e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:11.814ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="D^{2}A=\\mu _{0}J" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p>In geometric calculus, juxtapositioning of vectors such as in <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle DF}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7c00d6204f2d95ede007728da3d08679156a5340" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.686ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="DF" /></span> indicate the geometric product and can be decomposed into parts as <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle DF=D\\cdot F+D\\wedge F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/897561174a9d743984871fdec5d47fd6a58ef479" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:21.3ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="DF=D\\cdot F+D\\wedge F" /></span>. Here <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f34a0c600395e5d4345287e21fb26efd386990e6" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.935ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="D" /></span> is the covector derivative in any spacetime and reduces to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a3d0e93b78c50237f9ea83d027e4ebbdaef354b2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.946ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\nabla " /></span> in flat spacetime. Where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo>&#x25BD;<!-- \xe2\x96\xbd --></mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\bigtriangledown }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f0a807766385f70af07e77a0d7eab90b8c271ab1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:2.076ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="\\bigtriangledown " /></span> plays a role in Minkowski <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 4}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/295b4bf1de7cd3500e740e0f4f0635db22d87b42" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="4" /></span>-spacetime which is synonymous to the role of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a3d0e93b78c50237f9ea83d027e4ebbdaef354b2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.946ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\nabla " /></span> in Euclidean <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 3}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/991e33c6e207b12546f15bdfee8b5726eafbbb2f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="3" /></span>-space and is related to the <a href="/wiki/D%27Alembertian" class="mw-redirect" title="D\'Alembertian">d\'Alembertian</a> by <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x25FB;<!-- \xe2\x97\xbb --></mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mo>&#x25BD;<!-- \xe2\x96\xbd --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\Box =\\bigtriangledown ^{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/048d26719e87d3962b31ca5213df888dd52f7fb0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:8.066ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="\\Box =\\bigtriangledown ^{2}" /></span>. Indeed, given an observer represented by a future pointing timelike vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\gamma _{0}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/407f2fbc64e21bb432f397fdb816de0f5083d900" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:2.276ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\gamma _{0}" /></span> we have</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x25BD;<!-- \xe2\x96\xbd --></mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\gamma _{0}\\cdot \\bigtriangledown ={\\frac {1}{c}}{\\frac {\\partial }{\\partial t}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/80cf1dedc34a732ee65334d9bf192b92ba0ce782" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:14.175ex; height:5.509ex;" alt="\\gamma _{0}\\cdot \\bigtriangledown ={\\frac {1}{c}}{\\frac {\\partial }{\\partial t}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B3;<!-- \xce\xb3 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x25BD;<!-- \xe2\x96\xbd --></mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\gamma _{0}\\wedge \\bigtriangledown =\\nabla }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2b814a3d585d48d167a5f7fab70c4a422080b227" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:12.001ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="\\gamma _{0}\\wedge \\bigtriangledown =\\nabla " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Lorentz_boost" class="mw-redirect" title="Lorentz boost">Boosts</a> in this Lorentzian metric space have the same expression <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>&#x03B2;<!-- \xce\xb2 --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e^{\\beta }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/828688a27628ed5f06a50a9c9f161c85238f953c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.275ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="e^{\\beta }" /></span> as rotation in Euclidean space, where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi>&#x03B2;<!-- \xce\xb2 --></mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\beta }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4f08e5bb6adcac8ac464df79e6a2e43779898ab7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.342ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\beta }" /></span> is the bivector generated by the time and the space directions involved, whereas in the Euclidean case it is the bivector generated by the two space directions, strengthening the "analogy" to almost identity.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Relationship_with_other_formalisms">Relationship with other formalisms</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Relationship with other formalisms">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2ab72edce2f9250739288e98ab783313534f9fbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.623ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)" /></span> may be <a href="/wiki/Comparison_of_vector_algebra_and_geometric_algebra" title="Comparison of vector algebra and geometric algebra">directly compared</a> to <a href="/wiki/Vector_calculus#Algebraic_operations" title="Vector calculus">vector algebra</a>.</p>\n<p>The <a href="/wiki/Even_subalgebra" class="mw-redirect" title="Even subalgebra">even subalgebra</a> of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(2,0)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d9ccbfb54c452f15e49fe599a353f0e44839e473" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.623ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {G}}(2,0)" /></span> is isomorphic to the <a href="/wiki/Complex_number" title="Complex number">complex numbers</a>, as may be seen by writing a vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle P}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b4dc73bf40314945ff376bd363916a738548d40a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.756ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="P" /></span> in terms of its components in an orthonormal basis and left multiplying by the basis vector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e_{1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6e81caf3d4bcb929315801cbabc83543829484ee" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.156ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="e_{1}" /></span>, yielding</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>Z</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>y</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>y</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle Z=e_{1}P=e_{1}(xe_{1}+ye_{2})=x(1)+y(e_{1}e_{2}),}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b7e7482d9e5237b12591d1ccfb9a3a6c1b1e527f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:43.742ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle Z=e_{1}P=e_{1}(xe_{1}+ye_{2})=x(1)+y(e_{1}e_{2}),}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>where we identify <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle i\\mapsto e_{1}e_{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/38fe462cc918393dda75ae1fd43ee9fbd29c6913" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:8.749ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle i\\mapsto e_{1}e_{2}}" /></span> since</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mn>1.</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle ({e_{1}}{e_{2}})^{2}={e_{1}}{e_{2}}{e_{1}}{e_{2}}=-{e_{1}}{e_{1}}{e_{2}}{e_{2}}=-1.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cdd292c54a2969aa62480fdb7b39db2a0e7c55d7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:39.242ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle ({e_{1}}{e_{2}})^{2}={e_{1}}{e_{2}}{e_{1}}{e_{2}}=-{e_{1}}{e_{1}}{e_{2}}{e_{2}}=-1.}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Similarly, the even subalgebra of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2ab72edce2f9250739288e98ab783313534f9fbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.623ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)" /></span> with basis <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{1,e_{2}e_{3},e_{3}e_{1},e_{1}e_{2}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/dd59b5bb597e47d7f6a5d120cae489ee4ddd59d9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:19.585ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\{1,e_{2}e_{3},e_{3}e_{1},e_{1}e_{2}\\}}" /></span> is isomorphic to the <a href="/wiki/Quaternion" title="Quaternion">quaternions</a> as may be seen by identifying <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle i\\mapsto -e_{2}e_{3}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cecd02ce22cbc0bea294574db9ee762852dcae7f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:10.567ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle i\\mapsto -e_{2}e_{3}}" /></span>, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>j</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle j\\mapsto -e_{3}e_{1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d27a26ec2b30cf0ce2ff1c1aaae2cdf95d7293bd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.016ex; width:10.739ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle j\\mapsto -e_{3}e_{1}}" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle k\\mapsto -e_{1}e_{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1018054ad672c3f77de4fd12c7c41c09253cc6b9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:10.976ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle k\\mapsto -e_{1}e_{2}}" /></span>.</p>\n<p>Every <a href="/wiki/Associative_algebra" title="Associative algebra">associative algebra</a> has a matrix representation; the <a href="/wiki/Pauli_matrices" title="Pauli matrices">Pauli matrices</a> are a representation of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2ab72edce2f9250739288e98ab783313534f9fbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.623ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)" /></span> and the <a href="/wiki/Dirac_matrices" class="mw-redirect" title="Dirac matrices">Dirac matrices</a> are a representation of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(1,3)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5dd3fb30002bf84a4315105571e473f68cbdf4b7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.623ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {G}}(1,3)" /></span>, showing the equivalence with matrix representations used by physicists.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Geometric_calculus">Geometric calculus</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Geometric calculus">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Geometric_calculus" title="Geometric calculus">Geometric calculus</a></div>\n<p>Geometric calculus extends the formalism to include differentiation and integration including differential geometry and differential forms.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHestenesSobczyk1984_21-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEHestenesSobczyk1984-21">[13]</a></sup></p>\n<p>Essentially, the vector derivative is defined so that the GA version of <a href="/wiki/Green%27s_theorem" title="Green\'s theorem">Green\'s theorem</a> is true,</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>A</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n            <mi>A</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>f</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\int _{A}dA\\,\\nabla f=\\oint _{\\partial A}dx\\,f}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ab84432295735ce53f42cc0f6ed630eb41d692ea" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:21.218ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\int _{A}dA\\,\\nabla f=\\oint _{\\partial A}dx\\,f}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and then one can write</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla f=\\nabla \\cdot f+\\nabla \\wedge f}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1eb975df2e494fb2cdb0fe256517b7ed496aed3f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:19.948ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\\nabla f=\\nabla \\cdot f+\\nabla \\wedge f" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>as a geometric product, effectively generalizing <a href="/wiki/Stokes%27_theorem" title="Stokes\' theorem">Stokes\' theorem</a> (including the differential form version of it).</p>\n<p>In <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 1D}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5f1238338b91ef0b604a8946d6a140366e7bf3b4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.108ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="1D" /></span> when <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7daff47fa58cdfd29dc333def748ff5fa4c923e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.754ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="A" /></span> is a curve with endpoints <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>b</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle b}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f11423fbb2e967f986e36804a8ae4271734917c3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.008ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="b" /></span>, then</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>A</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n            <mi>A</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>f</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\int _{A}dA\\,\\nabla f=\\oint _{\\partial A}dx\\,f}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ab84432295735ce53f42cc0f6ed630eb41d692ea" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:21.218ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\int _{A}dA\\,\\nabla f=\\oint _{\\partial A}dx\\,f}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>reduces to</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msubsup>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\int _{a}^{b}dx\\,\\nabla f=\\int _{a}^{b}dx\\cdot \\nabla f=\\int _{a}^{b}df=f(b)-f(a)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/083f4183527d4ba974a642009cf4b82b22406630" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:48.28ex; height:6.343ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\int _{a}^{b}dx\\,\\nabla f=\\int _{a}^{b}dx\\cdot \\nabla f=\\int _{a}^{b}df=f(b)-f(a)}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>or the fundamental theorem of integral calculus.</p>\n<p>Also developed are the concept of vector manifold and geometric integration theory (which generalizes Cartan\'s differential forms).</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Conformal_geometric_algebra_.28CGA.29">Conformal geometric algebra (CGA)</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Conformal geometric algebra (CGA)">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Conformal_geometric_algebra" title="Conformal geometric algebra">Conformal geometric algebra</a></div>\n<p>A compact description of the current state of the art is provided by <a href="#CITEREFBayro-CorrochanoScheuermann2010">Bayro-Corrochano &amp; Scheuermann (2010)</a>, which also includes further references, in particular to <a href="#CITEREFDorstFontijneMann2007">Dorst, Fontijne &amp; Mann (2007)</a>. Other useful references are <a href="#CITEREFLi2008">Li (2008)</a> and <a href="#CITEREFBayro-Corrochano2010">Bayro-Corrochano (2010)</a>.</p>\n<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/File:Conformal_Embedding.svg" class="image"><img alt="Conformal Embedding.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Conformal_Embedding.svg/300px-Conformal_Embedding.svg.png" width="300" height="256" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Conformal_Embedding.svg/450px-Conformal_Embedding.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Conformal_Embedding.svg/600px-Conformal_Embedding.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="525" data-file-height="448" /></a></div>\n<p>Working within GA, Euclidean space <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">E</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {E}}^{3}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7231bd90cf13b0002083b700e4b88a96da18644f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.408ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {E}}^{3}" /></span> is embedded projectively in the CGA <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>4</mn>\n            <mo>,</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}^{4,1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0c55e29af696cc18ca9b4393f0f4d75229e9cffb" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:3.762ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {G}}^{4,1}" /></span> via the identification of Euclidean points with <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/92d98b82a3778f043108d4e20960a9193df57cbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="1" /></span>-d subspaces in the <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 4}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/295b4bf1de7cd3500e740e0f4f0635db22d87b42" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="4" /></span>-d null cone of the <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>5</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 5}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/29483407999b8763f0ea335cf715a6a5e809f44b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.173ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="5" /></span>-d CGA vector subspace, and adding a point at infinity. This allows all conformal transformations to be done as rotations and reflections and is <a href="/wiki/Covariance_and_contravariance_of_vectors" title="Covariance and contravariance of vectors">covariant</a>, extending incidence relations of projective geometry to circles and spheres.</p>\n<p>Specifically, we add orthogonal basis vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e_{+}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/fa5788d64b639ac33ae787ed11fad9db50202790" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.612ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle e_{+}}" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e_{-}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cbbe43293c4e2e3db838f7e02ad81ee4f489966d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.049ex; margin-bottom: -0.623ex; width:2.612ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle e_{-}}" /></span> such that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mo>+</mo>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {e_{+}}^{2}=+1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/681693ca80cc70f366308713df8efedf35ff1163" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:9.774ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {e_{+}}^{2}=+1}" /></span> and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {e_{-}}^{2}=-1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d6afc2f90ff931f62f3fe08ab0143228115cded0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.049ex; margin-bottom: -0.623ex; width:9.774ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {e_{-}}^{2}=-1}" /></span> to the basis of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">G</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2ab72edce2f9250739288e98ab783313534f9fbf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.623ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {G}}(3,0)" /></span> and identify <a href="/wiki/Null_vectors" class="mw-redirect" title="Null vectors">null vectors</a></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>n</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x221E;<!-- \xe2\x88\x9e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n_{\\infty }=e_{-}+e_{+}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cfdaabc55caa91a52e1363c0ded3c2cffc69f604" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:14.472ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="n_{\\infty }=e_{-}+e_{+}" /></span> as an <a href="/wiki/Ideal_point" title="Ideal point">ideal point</a> (point at infinity) (see <a href="/wiki/Compactification_(mathematics)" title="Compactification (mathematics)">Compactification</a>) and</dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>n</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtext>o</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mstyle>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n_{\\text{o}}={\\tfrac {1}{2}}(e_{-}-e_{+})}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0b28c158afe486baa499d9747e2f084c3bb62dd4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:17.147ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle n_{\\text{o}}={\\tfrac {1}{2}}(e_{-}-e_{+})}" /></span> as the point at the origin, giving</dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>n</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x221E;<!-- \xe2\x88\x9e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>n</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtext>o</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n_{\\infty }\\cdot n_{\\text{o}}=-1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4f9384535bec35b94a241d3eb65478ca54954777" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:13.545ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle n_{\\infty }\\cdot n_{\\text{o}}=-1}" /></span>.</dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This procedure has some similarities to the procedure for working with <a href="/wiki/Homogeneous_coordinates" title="Homogeneous coordinates">homogeneous coordinates</a> in projective geometry and in this case allows the modeling of <a href="/wiki/Euclidean_transformation" class="mw-redirect" title="Euclidean transformation">Euclidean transformations</a> as <a href="/wiki/Orthogonal_transformation" title="Orthogonal transformation">orthogonal transformations</a>.</p>\n<p>A fast changing and fluid area of GA, CGA is also being investigated for applications to relativistic physics.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="History">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: History">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl>\n<dt>Before the 20th century</dt>\n</dl>\n<p>Although the connection of geometry with algebra dates as far back at least to <a href="/wiki/Euclid" title="Euclid">Euclid</a>\'s <i><a href="/wiki/Euclid%27s_Elements" title="Euclid\'s Elements">Elements</a></i> in the third century B.C. (see <a href="/wiki/History_of_elementary_algebra#Greek_geometric_algebra" class="mw-redirect" title="History of elementary algebra">Greek geometric algebra</a>), GA in the sense used in this article was not developed until 1844, when it was used in a <i>systematic way</i> to describe the geometrical properties and <i>transformations</i> of a space. In that year, <a href="/wiki/Hermann_Grassmann" title="Hermann Grassmann">Hermann Grassmann</a> introduced the idea of a geometrical algebra in full generality as a certain calculus (analogous to the <a href="/wiki/Propositional_calculus" title="Propositional calculus">propositional calculus</a>) that encoded all of the geometrical information of a space.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGrassmann1844_22-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGrassmann1844-22">[14]</a></sup> Grassmann\'s algebraic system could be applied to a number of different kinds of spaces, the chief among them being <a href="/wiki/Euclidean_space" title="Euclidean space">Euclidean space</a>, <a href="/wiki/Affine_space" title="Affine space">affine space</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Projective_space" title="Projective space">projective space</a>. Following Grassmann, in 1878 <a href="/wiki/William_Kingdon_Clifford" title="William Kingdon Clifford">William Kingdon Clifford</a> examined Grassmann\'s algebraic system alongside the <a href="/wiki/Quaternions" class="mw-redirect" title="Quaternions">quaternions</a> of <a href="/wiki/William_Rowan_Hamilton" title="William Rowan Hamilton">William Rowan Hamilton</a> in (<a href="#CITEREFClifford1878">Clifford 1878</a>). From his point of view, the quaternions described certain <i>transformations</i> (which he called <i>rotors</i>), whereas Grassmann\'s algebra described certain <i>properties</i> (or <i>Strecken</i> such as length, area, and volume). His contribution was to define a new product \xe2\x80\x94&#160;the <i>geometric product</i>&#160;\xe2\x80\x93 on an existing Grassmann algebra, which realized the quaternions as living within that algebra. Subsequently, <a href="/wiki/Rudolf_Lipschitz" title="Rudolf Lipschitz">Rudolf Lipschitz</a> in 1886 generalized Clifford\'s interpretation of the quaternions and applied them to the geometry of rotations in <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.405ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="n" /></span> dimensions. Later these developments would lead other 20th-century mathematicians to formalize and explore the properties of the Clifford algebra.</p>\n<p>Nevertheless, another revolutionary development of the 19th-century would completely overshadow the geometric algebras: that of <a href="/wiki/Vector_analysis" class="mw-redirect" title="Vector analysis">vector analysis</a>, developed independently by <a href="/wiki/Josiah_Willard_Gibbs" title="Josiah Willard Gibbs">Josiah Willard Gibbs</a> and <a href="/wiki/Oliver_Heaviside" title="Oliver Heaviside">Oliver Heaviside</a>. Vector analysis was motivated by <a href="/wiki/James_Clerk_Maxwell" title="James Clerk Maxwell">James Clerk Maxwell</a>\'s studies of <a href="/wiki/Electromagnetism" title="Electromagnetism">electromagnetism</a>, and specifically the need to express and manipulate conveniently certain <a href="/wiki/Differential_equation" title="Differential equation">differential equations</a>. Vector analysis had a certain intuitive appeal compared to the rigors of the new algebras. Physicists and mathematicians alike readily adopted it as their geometrical toolkit of choice, particularly following the influential 1901 textbook <i><a href="/wiki/Vector_Analysis" title="Vector Analysis">Vector Analysis</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Edwin_Bidwell_Wilson" title="Edwin Bidwell Wilson">Edwin Bidwell Wilson</a>, following lectures of Gibbs.</p>\n<p>In more detail, there have been three approaches to geometric algebra: <a href="/wiki/Quaternion" title="Quaternion">quaternionic</a> analysis, initiated by Hamilton in 1843 and geometrized as rotors by Clifford in 1878; geometric algebra, initiated by Grassmann in 1844; and vector analysis, developed out of quaternionic analysis in the late 19th century by Gibbs and Heaviside. The legacy of quaternionic analysis in vector analysis can be seen in the use of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>i</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle i}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/add78d8608ad86e54951b8c8bd6c8d8416533d20" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:0.813ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="i" /></span>, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>j</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle j}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2f461e54f5c093e92a55547b9764291390f0b5d0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.016ex; width:0.985ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="j" /></span>, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>k</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle k}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c3c9a2c7b599b37105512c5d570edc034056dd40" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.222ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="k" /></span> to indicate the basis vectors of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="bold">R</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathbf {R} ^{3}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/42ee047387e551a89e8481e1a9e974dcc5fd5acc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.075ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="\\mathbf{R}^3" /></span>: it is being thought of as the purely imaginary quaternions. From the perspective of geometric algebra, <a href="/wiki/Quaternion#Quaternions_as_the_even_part_of_C.E2.84.933.2C0.28R.29" title="Quaternion">quaternions can be identified as Cl<span style="display:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height:1;font-size:80%;text-align:left">[0]<br />\n3,0</span>(<b>R</b>)</a>, the even part of the Clifford algebra on Euclidean 3-space, which unifies the three approaches.</p>\n<dl>\n<dt>20th century and present</dt>\n</dl>\n<p>Progress on the study of Clifford algebras quietly advanced through the twentieth century, although largely due to the work of <a href="/wiki/Abstract_algebra" title="Abstract algebra">abstract algebraists</a> such as <a href="/wiki/Hermann_Weyl" title="Hermann Weyl">Hermann Weyl</a> and <a href="/wiki/Claude_Chevalley" title="Claude Chevalley">Claude Chevalley</a>. The <i>geometrical</i> approach to geometric algebras has seen a number of 20th-century revivals. In mathematics, <a href="/wiki/Emil_Artin" title="Emil Artin">Emil Artin</a>\'s <i>Geometric Algebra</i><sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEArtin1957_23-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEArtin1957-23">[15]</a></sup> discusses the algebra associated with each of a number of geometries, including <a href="/wiki/Affine_geometry" title="Affine geometry">affine geometry</a>, <a href="/wiki/Projective_geometry" title="Projective geometry">projective geometry</a>, <a href="/wiki/Symplectic_geometry" title="Symplectic geometry">symplectic geometry</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Orthogonal_geometry" class="mw-redirect" title="Orthogonal geometry">orthogonal geometry</a>. In physics, geometric algebras have been revived as a "new" way to do classical mechanics and electromagnetism, together with more advanced topics such as quantum mechanics and gauge theory.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEDoran1994_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEDoran1994-2">[2]</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/David_Hestenes" title="David Hestenes">David Hestenes</a> reinterpreted the Pauli and Dirac matrices as vectors in ordinary space and spacetime, respectively, and has been a primary contemporary advocate for the use of geometric algebra.</p>\n<p>In <a href="/wiki/Computer_graphics" title="Computer graphics">computer graphics</a> and robotics, geometric algebras have been revived in order to efficiently represent rotations and other transformations. For applications of GA in robotics (screw theory, kinematics and dynamics using versors), computer vision, control and neural computing (geometric learning) see Bayro (2010).</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Software">Software</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: Software">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>GA is a very application-oriented subject. There is a reasonably steep initial learning curve associated with it, but this can be eased somewhat by the use of applicable software.</p>\n<p>The following is a list of freely available software that does not require ownership of commercial software or purchase of any commercial products for this purpose:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>GA Viewer <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.geometricalgebra.net/downloads.html">Fontijne, Dorst, Bouma &amp; Mann</a></li>\n<li>galgebra modules for <a href="/wiki/Sympy" class="mw-redirect" title="Sympy">sympy</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://github.com/brombo/galgebra">Alan Bromborsky</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The link provides a manual, introduction to GA and sample material as well as the software.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>CLUViz <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.clucalc.info/">Perwass</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Software allowing script creation and including sample visualizations, manual and GA introduction.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Gaigen <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/g25/" class="extiw" title="sourceforge:projects/g25/">Fontijne</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>For programmers, this is a code generator with support for C, C++, C# and Java.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cinderella Visualizations <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://erkenntnis.icu.ac.jp/gcj/software/GAcindy-1.4/GAcindy.htm">Hitzer</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://staff.science.uva.nl/~leo/cinderella/">Dorst</a>.</li>\n<li>Gaalop <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.gaalop.de/">[1]</a> Standalone GUI-Application that uses the Open-Source Computer Algebra Software <a href="/wiki/Maxima_(software)" title="Maxima (software)">Maxima</a> to break down CLUViz code into C/C++ or Java code.</li>\n<li>Gaalop Precompiler <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.gaalop.de/">[2]</a> Precompiler based on Gaalop integrated with <a href="/wiki/CMake" title="CMake">CMake</a>.</li>\n<li>Gaalet, C++ Expression Template Library <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/gaalet/">Seybold</a>.</li>\n<li>Versor <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://versor.mat.ucsb.edu/">Colapinto</a>, A lightweight templated C++ Library with an OpenGL interface for efficient geometric algebra programming in arbitrary metrics, including <a href="/wiki/Conformal_geometric_algebra" title="Conformal geometric algebra">conformal</a></li>\n<li>Clifford Algebra with <a href="/wiki/Wolfram_Language" title="Wolfram Language">Mathematica</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://arxiv.org/abs/0810.2412">clifford.m</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Comparison_of_vector_algebra_and_geometric_algebra" title="Comparison of vector algebra and geometric algebra">Comparison of vector algebra and geometric algebra</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Clifford_algebra" title="Clifford algebra">Clifford algebra</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Spacetime_algebra" title="Spacetime algebra">Spacetime algebra</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Spinor" title="Spinor">Spinor</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Quaternion" title="Quaternion">Quaternion</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Algebra_of_physical_space" title="Algebra of physical space">Algebra of physical space</a> (<a href="https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Physics_in_the_Language_of_Geometric_Algebra._An_Approach_with_the_Algebra_of_Physical_Space" class="extiw" title="wikibooks:Physics in the Language of Geometric Algebra. An Approach with the Algebra of Physical Space">wikibooks:Physics in the Language of Geometric Algebra. An Approach with the Algebra of Physical Space</a>)</li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Universal_geometric_algebra" title="Universal geometric algebra">Universal geometric algebra</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Given <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <msup>\n            <mi>u</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle u^{2}=1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ba528fdfee161784e3cf5d10d601f272103f8515" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:6.684ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\textstyle u^{2}=1}" /></span>, we have that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <msup>\n            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle ({\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u))^{2}={\\frac {1}{4}}(1+2u+uu)={\\frac {1}{4}}(1+2u+1)={\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/10748dd87f1dd400f670529b66ea34e4f7d2b729" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.338ex; width:59.558ex; height:3.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\textstyle ({\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u))^{2}={\\frac {1}{4}}(1+2u+uu)={\\frac {1}{4}}(1+2u+1)={\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u)}" /></span>, showing that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle {\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/75e64e11935d0246acfe1f13db75405a3031f788" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:8.86ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\textstyle {\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u)}" /></span> is idempotent, and that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>0</mn>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle {\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u)(1-u)={\\frac {1}{2}}(1-uu)={\\frac {1}{2}}(1-1)=0}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/167e8228a39adb548121331c0c02d1a88e078b2e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:45.445ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\textstyle {\\frac {1}{2}}(1+u)(1-u)={\\frac {1}{2}}(1-uu)={\\frac {1}{2}}(1-1)=0}" /></span>, showing that it is a nonzero zero divisor.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">This should not be confused with Hestenes\'s irregular generalization <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <mi>C</mi>\n          <msub>\n            <mo>&#x2219;<!-- \xe2\x88\x99 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>H</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n          <mi>D</mi>\n          <mo>:=</mo>\n          <munder>\n            <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \xe2\x88\x91 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>r</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2260;<!-- \xe2\x89\xa0 --></mo>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n              <mo>,</mo>\n              <mi>s</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2260;<!-- \xe2\x89\xa0 --></mo>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </munder>\n          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n          <mi>C</mi>\n          <msub>\n            <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>r</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n          <mi>D</mi>\n          <msub>\n            <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>s</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n          <msub>\n            <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n              </mrow>\n              <mi>s</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle C\\bullet _{H}D:=\\sum _{r\\neq 0,s\\neq 0}\\langle \\langle C\\rangle _{r}\\langle D\\rangle _{s}\\rangle _{|s-r|}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9f1a8ee346e693a33409f8a4f0c075bbf9b4dfda" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.338ex; width:35.47ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\textstyle C\\bullet _{H}D:=\\sum _{r\\neq 0,s\\neq 0}\\langle \\langle C\\rangle _{r}\\langle D\\rangle _{s}\\rangle _{|s-r|}}" /></span>, where the distinguishing notation is from <a href="#CITEREFDorstFontijneMann2007">Dorst, Fontijne &amp; Mann (2007)</a>, \xc2\xa7B.1 p. 590, which makes the point that scalar components must be handled separately with this product.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">When referring to grading under the geometric product, the literature generally only focuses on a <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">Z</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} _{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6db12380c9729e73f72c94f7c4b7745406c4e0d7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.492ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} _{2}}" /></span>-grading, meaning the split into even and odd <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">Z</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/faf96082c4b2e79d67626f995ae571403f51b5da" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.431ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\\mathrm  {Z}}" /></span>-grades. <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">Z</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} _{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6db12380c9729e73f72c94f7c4b7745406c4e0d7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.492ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} _{2}}" /></span> is a subgroup of the full <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">Z</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} _{2}{}^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/60a8157b235894d5d0753f7a6eaa4ccb644c2c04" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:3.718ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Z} _{2}{}^{n}}" /></span>-grading of the geometric product.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">This definition follows <a href="#CITEREFDorst2007">Dorst (2007)</a> and <a href="#CITEREFPerwass2009">Perwass (2009)</a> \xe2\x80\x93 the left contraction used by Dorst replaces the ("fat dot") inner product that Perwass uses, consistent with Perwass\'s constraint that grade of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7daff47fa58cdfd29dc333def748ff5fa4c923e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.754ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="A" /></span> may not exceed that of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Dorst appears to merely assume <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B^{+}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/731dc88dd44f84be3617c27615bcc6840c2aeeb0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.293ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="B^{{+}}" /></span> such that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{+}=1}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/fad345f7ff9b2f36f485730aad76cb8256b1e544" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:11.682ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle B\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{+}=1}" /></span>, whereas <a href="#CITEREFPerwass2009">Perwass (2009)</a> defines <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B^{+}=B^{\\dagger }/(B\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{\\dagger })}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/61bec122222d65f4a0cff0cb2c3f6cbb82aca44d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:19.001ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle B^{+}=B^{\\dagger }/(B\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{\\dagger })}" /></span>, where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B^{\\dagger }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/677130bc88d995143eea4e7e2daeff0dcc7e73db" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.744ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle B^{\\dagger }}" /></span> is the conjugate of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>, equivalent to the reverse of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span> up to a sign.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">That is to say, the projection must be defined as <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{+})\\;\\rfloor \\;B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f8eb97cc49a24a7ed8c03425601c0d57a5a16656" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.125ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{+})\\;\\rfloor \\;B}" /></span> and not as <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x230B;<!-- \xe2\x8c\x8b --></mo>\n        <mspace width="thickmathspace" />\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>+</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (A\\;\\rfloor \\;B)\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{+}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/29d8d19f4239cfad03f6ab3dfaf7b80932283cd0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:13.317ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\\displaystyle (A\\;\\rfloor \\;B)\\;\\rfloor \\;B^{+}}" /></span>, though the two are equivalent for non-null blades <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47136aad860d145f75f3eed3022df827cee94d7a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.774ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="B" /></span>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">This generalization to all <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7daff47fa58cdfd29dc333def748ff5fa4c923e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.754ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="A" /></span> is apparently not considered by Perwass or Dorst.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-19"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Perwass also claims here that David Hestenes coined the term "versor", where he is presumably referring to the GA context (the term <a href="/wiki/Versor" title="Versor">versor</a> appears to have been used by <a href="/wiki/William_Rowan_Hamilton" title="William Rowan Hamilton">Hamilton</a> to refer to a related object of the <a href="/wiki/Quaternion" title="Quaternion">quaternion</a> algebra).</span></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Citations">Citations</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_algebra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Citations">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id